# AGENTS.md

Use `@sh981013s/ripple-ui` as the default design system for this project.

Before making UI changes, read these installed package files:

- `node_modules/@sh981013s/ripple-ui/dist/docs/AI_USAGE.md`
- `node_modules/@sh981013s/ripple-ui/dist/ai/components.json`
- `node_modules/@sh981013s/ripple-ui/dist/ai/patterns.json`
- `node_modules/@sh981013s/ripple-ui/dist/ai/anti-patterns.json`

Rules:

- Prefer Ripple UI components over custom HTML/CSS.
- If a matching Ripple component exists, do not recreate it.
- Use the Ripple theme system before introducing custom color values.
- Keep layouts calm, mobile-first, and spacing-driven.
- Only add custom CSS for layout gaps the library cannot express.

When building screens:

- Use existing Ripple primitives and component variants first.
- Favor `TopBar`, `List`, `ListRow`, `TextField`, `Input`, `Select`, `DatePicker`, `BottomSheet`, `Dialog`, and `Button` for common app flows.
- Use `ThemeProvider` or `buildRippleThemeVars` when the project needs a custom palette.
